parameters:
Karin-chan, are you going out? If you need me, please take
me with you. I'm sure I can be of help.

Good evening--Momiji-san, are you here? Thank you for
helping me at the bandit fort the other day.

Eh--!? Why do you know my mother's name? No, you're
mistaken, I'm Karin!

...I see. Karin-chan, you were alive. I could hardly believe
it until now, but seeing you like this, I'm convinced.
You've done well to stay safe all this time...

Whoa!? What's the matter, Momiji-san? Why are you suddenly
hugging me--!? ...!?

...I'm sorry. I didn't think you were the Karin-chan I knew.
To think you were such a tiny baby back then, and now you've
grown so much...

...(Does Momiji-san know about my childhood? She doesn't
seem much older than me... How come...?)

Even so... you really do look just like Yorin-san. I've only
ever seen you with long hair, Karin-chan, but when you tie
it back, you're the spitting image of her. Is your mother
doing well?

My mother... she passed away shortly after I was born. So I
don't even know what she looked like...

...Is that so. Yorin-san was such a beautiful and kind
person. She took good care of me too... It's a shame she's
gone...
What about Chuutaro-san? Aren't you living with him now?

My father... he's been missing for five years... I'm still
looking for him, but I haven't found him yet...

That's terrible... Chuutaro-san too... It must have been
lonely without both parents. I'm sorry I couldn't be there
for you.

I have so many questions for you, Momiji-san. Why do the oni
known as the War Demons know about my father... I want to
know.

That is because we lived together with Karin-chan's family.
And that was over a hundred years ago--

Yes. There once was a small village deep in the mountains to
the east of Mount Fuji where about 300 people lived. The
name of that village was--

--Oh! Momiji-san, it's terrible! Another courtesan has gone
missing!

Yes. She disappeared along with a client from her room...
It's like she was spirited away. This makes it the third one
this month...
(So the stories about courtesans disappearing were true...)

Oh, who is this young lady? She has quite the... lovely
appearance?

I am [Kunoichi Karin] from the Iga Ninja Group directly
under the shogunate. I've come here to investigate the case
of the disappearing courtesans.

--Eh!? A retainer of the shogunate!? That's reassuring, but
how exactly do you plan to investigate these disappearances?
Surely not by...?

Yes. I will disguise myself as a courtesan and investigate
the case.

...!? Are you serious about becoming a courtesan, Karin-
chan?

Yes, I'm serious. If they go missing while alone in a room
with a client, then surely the perpetrator must be one of
the men who come to see the courtesans--

Hmm... We suspect our clients as well, but for business
reasons, we can't just not allow courtesans to be alone with
them, nor can we turn away someone just because they're
suspicious... Your offer is appreciated, but what will you
do if you're attacked?

If it were me, I could fight back even if attacked by a
client and I believe I could capture the perpetrator who's
been abducting courtesans. I've done undercover
investigations before, so there's no need to worry.

Ah! Really? Then I'll leave it to you, Kunoichi. Please find
and capture the perpetrator among the clients.

...Are you sure it's okay, Karin-chan? Undercover work in a
brothel isn't something to be taken lightly...

Don't worry, Momiji-san. I'll definitely catch them while
pretending to be a courtesan. The perpetrator might even be
an oni (whisper whisper)

...! If the courtesans are indeed being carried away through
the windows, then it's highly likely that the culprit isn't
an ordinary human. Understood. Please don't overdo it. If
you encounter the perpetrator, Karin-chan, I'll come running
immediately.

...? Are you really sure we can ask you to do an undercover
investigation? It's a dangerous job, being alone in a room
with the criminal, isn't it?

Yes! I will now work as a courtesan in the pleasure
district.

That's a relief! Then I'll give you [Courtesan's Kimono]. If
you wear this, you can work in the brothel at the very back.
Please find the criminal. I'm counting on you.

You only need to pretend to be a courtesan, okay? If a
customer approaches you, you can always turn them down.
Please don't push yourself too hard, Karin-chan...

[Letter] To Momiji, I will be waiting at the graveyard of
the old red-light district. Come alone--Kotaro

A letter from Kotaro--!? Could it be... Momiji-san went
there alone...!? I have to chase after her right away!

--Karin contacted Yugiri and Masaki and headed for the
[Abandoned Red-Light District]!

What the--!? Momiji is covered in blood!? What on earth
happened here!?

Hmph, as expected of someone who has buried five battle
demons so far. You seem to have the strength to see through
such traps.
That's cowardly! Using Momiji-san as bait like that!?

...Cowardly? What's wrong with being cowardly. That is the
way of us ninjas of the warring states.

Spreading rumors in a town under enemy control, making
people suspicious and fearful, setting fire to the enemy's
castle under cover of night, causing chaos, and sometimes
coldly assassinating the enemy lord in his sleep along with
his concubines--that is our ninja work.

Your father, Chuutaro, was indeed the strongest ninja of the
warring states. You grew up ignorant of his true nature. Did
you grow up comfortably without ever hearing about your
father's deeds?

~~~~!! Do you know where my father is!? Where is he now!?
Answer me!?

I told you when we fought at the Atami seaside cave, didn't
I? Chuutaro is dead--don't make me say it again.

Lies--! I can't believe that! I've lived this long just to
see my father again! Don't spout nonsense!

You never learn, girl. Then I shall kill you here--reunite
with your father in the afterlife.
Momiji-dono? Thank goodness! Are you conscious!?

You're the one who left Momiji covered in blood, aren't
you!? Unforgivable! How dare you do this to my disciple
Momiji--!

Hmph. It's a fitting punishment for a traitor. I intended to
kill her by inflicting pain, but the demon's genes are
indeed tenacious. Her heart seems to be faintly beating
still.

Due to the demon's unique regenerative abilities, it's not
easy for her to die. I should have stabbed her heart
multiple times instead of relying on my fists.

~~~~!! I will never forgive you! I'll return the pain you
inflicted on Momiji-san threefold!

Chuutaro's daughter, Karin. Someone like you is no match for
me! Take this! Raging Whirlwind Slash--!!
A slicing whirlwind--!? Ugh! I can't see in front of me!
Nooo~~! Being blown away by the wind!?

--Karin and the others were all blown away and slammed into
a tree!

That was just a greeting. I could have killed you all right
here, but I'll excuse myself for tonight. Dawn is
approaching, after all.

You're leaving at dawn...? I see. Demons melt in the
sunlight, don't they?

Ha! I once heard from a missionary from the foreign lands.
In his country, there are demons that drink blood and perish
in the sunlight--but we do not melt. Our demonic power is
too strong, and our vision too keen, making the bright light
simply inconvenient for battle. That's the only reason.
--Karin was slammed into the ground by Kotaro's fist!

(...! This demon warrior is completely different from the
others! No carelessness or openings! A strong and cunningly
troublesome opponent!)

The fight for tonight ends here. I'll take Momiji, who's
barely breathing, as a hostage.
Ku, Momiji-san...! Where do you intend to take her!?

To the depths of [Fuma Valley]--wait for us in the village
of Fuma. Come directly without any detours. Even Momiji,
with her strong regenerative demon powers, will die if she
continues to bleed out. Do not forget--
Wait! Where is this Fuma Valley located!?

Head west from Odawara, then go north from there. You'll
find it. Farewell. If you want to retrieve Momiji, the three
of you had better come.
--Kotaro grabbed Momiji by the head and leaped away!

...Damn it! To have Momiji taken away without being able to
do anything...!

We couldn't even land a single blow before letting him
escape. I never imagined Momiji-dono would be taken
hostage...

Gngh! How vexing! We must rescue the wounded Momiji--to Fuma
Valley we go, and quickly, Karin!

I know. Kotaro is an opponent we must defeat at all costs...
Let's head to Fuma Valley at dawn.

I thought you'd head to Fuji right away, but you're not
going yet? Hehe, that's so like you, Karin-chan. It seems
our master is sleeping well and accumulating mystical power.
Let's head to Fuji tomorrow.
